{
  "message": "Add secret type support for user-defined operator parameters (#5752)\n\n## Summary\n\nEnable user-defined operators (UDOs) in packages to declare parameters\nwith the `secret` type. This ensures that secret values are properly\nhandled as secret expressions and validates that only secret expressions\n(created with the `secret()` function) are passed to these parameters.\n\nPreviously, operator parameters could only be declared as field paths or\nuntyped. This enhancement improves security by allowing explicit\ndeclaration of sensitive parameters that must be secrets.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`libtenzir/src/package.cpp`**: Added handling for `secret` type in\n`parse_parameter_value_type()` function to recognize and convert secret\ntype declarations\n- **Test fixtures**: Added comprehensive test cases covering both\npositional and named secret parameters, including literal secret\nexpressions\n\n## Example Usage\n\nOperators can now declare secret parameters in their YAML definition:\n\n```yaml\nargs:\n  positional:\n    - name: api_key\n      type: secret\n      description: \"API key to use for authentication\"\n  named:\n    - name: token\n      type: secret\n      description: \"Authentication token\"\n```\n\nThen use them in the operator definition:\n\n```tql\nfrom {dummy: 1}\nmy_pkg::my_operator secret(\"const\", token=secret(\"my-token\"))\n```\n\n## Test Coverage\n\nAdded integration tests for:\n- `udo-args-typed-secret.tql` and `.txt` - Basic positional secret\nparameter test\n- `udo-args-typed-secret-literal.tql` and `.txt` - Positional secret\nwith literal value\n- `udo-args-named-typed-secret.tql` and `.txt` - Named secret parameter\ntest\n- `udo-args-named-typed-secret-literal.tql` and `.txt` - Named secret\nwith literal value\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with Claude Code",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "cf5880a094503eedd1da530761aa90828e76ed4d",
      "filename": "changelog/unreleased/secret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "status": "added",
      "additions": 19,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 19,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md?ref=1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8",
      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+---\n+title: Secret type support for user-defined operator parameters\n+type: bugfix\n+authors:\n+  - mavam\n+  - claude\n+pr: 5752\n+created: 2026-02-12T17:26:03.709677Z\n+---\n+\n+User-defined operators in packages can now declare parameters with the `secret` type to ensure that secret values are properly handled as secret expressions:\n+\n+```\n+args:\n+  positional:\n+    - name: api_key\n+      type: secret\n+      description: \"API key to use for authentication\"\n+```"
    },
    {
      "sha": "d0873f0c1fb32d7e96988606c587d7a8e48742e5",
      "filename": "libtenzir/src/package.cpp",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 3,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 3,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp?ref=1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8",
      "patch": "@@ -439,6 +439,9 @@ auto parse_parameter_value_type(const package_operator_parameter& param,\n   if (not param.type || is_field_path_type(param)) {\n     return std::optional<type>{};\n   }\n+  if (*param.type == \"secret\") {\n+    return std::optional<type>{type{secret_type{}}};\n+  }\n   // Using the legacy parser here because it is convenient.\n   // We will eventually add support for user defined operators in TQL itself and\n   // deprecate this approach, so it does not make sense to refactor the tql2"
    },
    {
      "sha": "7d9f51d01c17bf42cbafd281d25fa1ddd0691bc4",
      "filename": "libtenzir/src/tql2/user_defined_operator.cpp",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 20,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 20,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Ftql2%2Fuser_defined_operator.cpp",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Ftql2%2Fuser_defined_operator.cpp",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Ftql2%2Fuser_defined_operator.cpp?ref=1c8ddbcfb0f19095c957dfd5dcea668ad92846e8",
      "patch": "@@ -9,6 +9,7 @@\n #include \"tenzir/tql2/user_defined_operator.hpp\"\n \n #include \"tenzir/detail/similarity.hpp\"\n+#include \"tenzir/secret.hpp\"\n #include \"tenzir/tql2/ast.hpp\"\n #include \"tenzir/tql2/eval.hpp\"\n \n@@ -342,6 +343,23 @@ auto instantiate_user_defined_operator(const user_defined_operator& udo,\n   auto substitutions = std::unordered_map<std::string, ast::expression>{};\n   substitutions.reserve(udo.positional_params.size() + udo.named_params.size());\n \n+  auto coerce_const_string_to_secret =\n+    [&](const user_defined_operator::parameter& param, ast::expression& expr) {\n+      if (not param.value_type || not is<secret_type>(*param.value_type)) {\n+        return;\n+      }\n+      auto value = try_const_eval(expr, ctx);\n+      if (not value) {\n+        return;\n+      }\n+      auto* str = try_as<std::string>(&*value);\n+      if (not str) {\n+        return;\n+      }\n+      expr = ast::expression{\n+        ast::constant{secret::make_literal(*str), expr.get_location()}};\n+    };\n+\n   auto validate_type\n     = [&](const user_defined_operator::parameter& param,\n           const ast::expression& expr,\n@@ -377,6 +395,7 @@ auto instantiate_user_defined_operator(const user_defined_operator& udo,\n         return failure::promise();\n       }\n     }\n+    coerce_const_string_to_secret(param, expr);\n     if (not validate_type(param, expr, std::nullopt)) {\n       return failure::promise();\n     }\n@@ -402,6 +421,7 @@ auto instantiate_user_defined_operator(const user_defined_operator& udo,\n         return failure::promise();\n       }\n     }\n+    coerce_const_string_to_secret(param, value);\n     if (not validate_type(param, value, named_value_locations[i])) {\n       return failure::promise();\n     }"
    },
    {
      "sha": "4c2686f43c949c1e49ca19398c2c854540d5f30e",
